abstract: Improved demand for business products lifted results for the maker of computer networking equipment.
snippet: Improved demand for business products lifted results for the maker of computer networking equipment.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — John T. Chambers, chief executive of Cisco Systems, made one of his classic bombastic predictions Wednesday, claiming that the world’s largest maker of computer networking equipment is poised to dominate the construction of cloud computing systems.

headline.main: Cuts Help Cisco Beat Analysts’ Expectations
headline.print_headline: Cuts Help Cisco Beat Analysts’ Expectations
